# Clifford.Basic

Clifford algebra conventions for this project.

The Clifford algebra Cl(V, Q) for a quadratic form Q on a vector space V is the
associative algebra generated by V with relations:
  v * v = Q(v) • 1  for all v : V

This module documents the signature conventions used throughout the project and
provides lightweight wrappers over `Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.CliffordAlgebra`.

## Signature conventions

All Clifford algebras are parameterized by an explicit quadratic form. The default
Minkowski-signature module uses:
  Q(v) = v₀² - v₁² - v₂² - v₃²  (mostly-minus convention)

Euclidean signature uses:
  Q(v) = v₁² + … + vₙ²

Both conventions appear in the physics literature. Conventions are always explicit
parameters in this project; there are no hidden global choices.

Source: spin-geometry reference conventions from:
  - Lawson and Michelsohn, "Spin Geometry" (1989)
  - Baez and Huerta, "Division Algebras and Supersymmetry I", arXiv:0909.0551

Mathlib references:
  `Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.CliffordAlgebra.Basic`
  `Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.CliffordAlgebra.EvenOdd`
  `Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.CliffordAlgebra.SpinGroup`

Status: stub — convention wrappers to be added.
